Weekly Meeting Times: Mandatory weekly meetings will be held every Monday and Weds at 11:00 am in the ICS Labs (3rd Floor). Each meeting will be approximately one hour long.
If a team member is planning on missing the meeting, they need to email or text the team at least 24 hours prior.
If a team member expects to be late to a meeting (5 minutes or more), they will text at least one other member of the team.
If a team member is more than 20 minutes late without prior notice to the meeting, he/she will accept a punishment of the other team membersâ€™ choosing.

Code of Conduct:
Team members will equally distribute the work and provide constructive and timely feedback to each other.
If a teammate fails to contribute to the group assignments he/she will be confronted in a group meeting. Under extreme measures, the issue will be brought to the instructor if his/her contribution level does not improve.
Team members will be respectful towards each other.
Decisions will be made unanimously.
Team members will uphold the academic integrity of the UC-Irvine school system.

Communication:
Email: Team members are required to check their email at least twice a day.
Response Time: Team members will respond to emails within 24 hours of receipt.
Phone: Phone calls will be reserved for urgent matters only.
Texting: Text messages will be used for matters that need immediate responses.
Skype: If the team is unable to meet in person, a skype session will take place during the appropriate meeting time.
